Just upgraded JIRA from recent version to 6.3.3 as I keep up with all updates. Self hosted on Windows Server 2012 R2.  All has been working great but with the latest version, clicking an issue takes 5-10 seconds for the issue to load/appear.  Everything else runs fast, i.e. dashboard, etc.  It's just with issue opening.  I've locked/re-indexed, cycled the service, etc.  No luck.

FYI

h3. Summary
When right-clicking an issue on the Backlog view (context menu) of an Agile Board and selecting "View in Excel", it leads to a "404" page error.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Go to an existing Scrum board, or create a new one and link to a filter with ongoing issues;
# Navigate to the "Backlog" view;
# Right click on an issue and choose "View in Excel";
!view-in-excel.png|thumbnail!

h3. Expected Results
Given the recent removal of the feature that allowed exporting issues to Excel (see [JRA-61891|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-61891]), the context menu should instead present an option to export as CSV.

h3. Actual Results 
End up in a 404 page error.
!404-page-error.png|thumbnail!

h3. Workarounds
h5. Option #1 - View in Issue Navigator
# Choose "View in Issue Navigator";
# Use the exporting features available there, such as CSV;

h5. Option #2 - Re-enable Excel export
# Open the {{jira-config.properties}} file inside JIRA's [Home Directory|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/JIRA+Home+Directory] (or create it, if it doesn't exist);
# Add the below property to the file;
{code:none|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#6A8EB3|bgColor=#F8F8F8}
jira.export.excel.enabled = true
{code}
# Save the file;
# Restart JIRA;
